147954.name: Prevalence of underweight, weight for age (% of children under 5)
147954.description: Prevalence of underweight children is the percentage of children under age 5 whose weight for age is more than two standard deviations below the median for the international reference population ages 0-59 months. The data are based on the WHO's child growth standards released in 2006.

source.name: UNICEF, World Health Organization and World Bank
source.dataPublisherSource: Joint child malnutrition estimates - UNICEF / World Health Organization / World Bank
